<LG TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>[On Witchcraft and Dreams.]</HEAD>
<L>&YOGH;yf &thorn;ou euer<NOTE PLACE="foot">euere O.</NOTE> &thorn;urgh folye</L>
<L N="340">Dydyst ou&yogh;t<NOTE PLACE="foot">oght O, dedyst ony n. D.</NOTE> do nygr&oacute;mauncy.</L>
<L>Or to &thorn;e deuyl dedyst<NOTE PLACE="foot">dedist to &thorn;e deule D.</NOTE> sacryfyse</L>
<L>&THORN;urgh wychcraftys<NOTE PLACE="foot">wycchecraftys O, wycchecraft as &thorn;e on-wyse D.</NOTE> asyse,</L>
<L>Or any man &yogh;af<NOTE PLACE="foot">&yogh;afe O, &yogh;af D.</NOTE> &thorn;e mede<MILESTONE N="3a:2" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L N="344">For to reyse<NOTE PLACE="foot">reysyn D.</NOTE> &thorn;e deuyl yn dede,</L>
<L>For to telle, or for to wrey,<NOTE PLACE="foot">or to be wrey&yogh;e D.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;yng &thorn;at &thorn;e<NOTE PLACE="foot">&thorn;at &thorn;e O, &thorn;at HD.</NOTE> was don awey;<NOTE PLACE="foot">a wey&yogh;e D.</NOTE></L>
<L>&YOGH;yf &thorn;ou haue do any<NOTE PLACE="foot">don ony D.</NOTE> of &thorn;ys,</L>
<L N="348">&THORN;ou hast synned &amp; do<NOTE PLACE="foot">&thorn;an hast &thorn;ou synnyd &amp; don D.</NOTE> a-mys,</L>
<L>And<NOTE PLACE="foot">And <I>om</I>. D.</NOTE> &thorn;ou art wur&thorn;y<NOTE PLACE="foot">wr&thorn;y O, wur&thorn;i D.</NOTE> to be shent</L>
<L>&THORN;urgh &thorn;ys yche<NOTE PLACE="foot">for brekyng of &thorn;is D.</NOTE> commaund&euml;ment.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>&YOGH;yf you yn swerd, o&thorn;er<NOTE PLACE="foot">or OD.</NOTE> yn bacyn,</L>
<L N="352">Any chylde madyst<NOTE PLACE="foot">ony child dedyst D.</NOTE> loke &thorn;eryn,</L>
<L>Or yn &thorn;umbe,<NOTE PLACE="foot">tombe D.</NOTE> or yn cristal,&mdash;</L>
<L>wycch&euml;craft<NOTE PLACE="foot">. . . fte O, wycchecraft D.</NOTE> men clepyn<NOTE PLACE="foot">callyn D.</NOTE> hyt al:<NOTE PLACE="foot">al OD, alle H.</NOTE></L>
<L>Beleue nou&yogh;t<NOTE PLACE="foot">noght O, trowe not D.</NOTE> yn &thorn;e pyys cheteryng;<NOTE PLACE="foot">. . . nge O, py&yogh;es chateryng D.</NOTE></L>
<L N="356">Hyt ys no trou&thorn;e, but fals beleuyng.<NOTE PLACE="foot">. . . nge O, It ne is but fals &amp; lesyng D.</NOTE></L>
<L>Many beleuyn<NOTE PLACE="foot">trowyn D.</NOTE> yn &thorn;e pye:</L>
