</LG></NOTE></L>
<L N="371">Me &thorn;ynke&thorn; hyt ys fals<NOTE PLACE="foot">hyt fals O, for it is fals D.</NOTE> euery deyl,</L>
<L>Y beleue hyt nou&yogh;t, ne neuer shal weyl.<NOTE PLACE="foot">I trowe it not ne neuere wil D.</NOTE></L>
<L>For many hauyn glad hancel at<NOTE PLACE="foot">Many han hansele on D.</NOTE> &thorn;e morw,<NOTE PLACE="foot">morue O.</NOTE></L>
<L>And to hem or euyn com&thorn;<NOTE PLACE="foot">comy&thorn; O.</NOTE> mochyl<NOTE PLACE="foot">&thorn;at longe or euyn han sum D.</NOTE> sorw;<NOTE PLACE="foot">sorue O.</NOTE></L>
<L>And manyon hauyn yn &thorn;e day grete noy,<NOTE PLACE="foot">gret noye O, &amp; manye han al day meche noy&yogh;e D.</NOTE></L>
