<L>&THORN;at nou&yogh;t ys, ne neuer shal be;<MILESTONE N="3b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>And oft&euml;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Harl</I>. oft, oftyn D.</NOTE> mayst &thorn;ou fynde hyt ryght<NOTE PLACE="foot">ry&thorn;t O.</NOTE></L>
<L N="384">&thorn;at &thorn;ou hast mete vpon<NOTE PLACE="foot">mette opon O, mett of on D.</NOTE> &thorn;e nyght.<NOTE PLACE="foot">ny&thorn;t O.</NOTE></L>
<L>But &thorn;erof to haue mochyl<NOTE PLACE="foot">But ouer mochyl to haue &thorn;er on. O; but haue &thorn;erin non D.</NOTE> affyaunce</L>
